 philosophy is unconnected to our Western philosophical tradition, the contributors prove that nothing could be further from the truth. The most respected scholars in the field—George Allan, Lisa Bellantoni, John B. Cobb Jr., Frederick Ferré, David L. Hall, William S. Hamrick, Robert Cummings Neville, Janusz A. Polanowski, Patrick Shade, and Donald W. Sherburne—illustrate points of connection between Whitehead's ideas to the following: Descartes, the so-called "Father of Modern Philosophy"; classical American thought; several contemporary American thinkers, including Richard Rorty and Alasdair MacIntyre; aspects of European philosophy; and current reflections upon the environment and technology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPhilosophy, Modern. 4aPhilosophy : American Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Religion. 4aPhilosophy : Process Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh1 aAllan, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellantoni, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCobb, John B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerré, Frederick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, David Ray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, David L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamrick, William S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeville, Robert Cummings, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPolanowski, Janusz A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPolanowski, Janusz A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShade, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb